SwiftyRedis is a high level async redis library for Swift. It is partially rewritten and heavily inspired by the

It provides convenient access to all Redis functionality through a very flexible but low-level API. It has a customizable type conversion protocol so that any operation can return results in just the type you are expecting.
This makes for a very pleasant development experience.
Used to convert a value into one or multiple redis argument
strings. Most values will produce exactly one item but in
some cases it might make sense to produce more than one.
This writes the value into an Array of bytes.  Each item
is a single argument.  Most items generate a single item.
The exception to this rule currently are Arrays of items.
